Psalm 141-1 <pb/><t>O LORD, I call upon you; <f>ⓐ</f>hasten to me! </t><t>Give ear to my voice when I call to you!</t>
Psalm 141-2 <t>Let <f>ⓑ</f>my prayer be counted as incense before you, </t><t>and <f>ⓒ</f>the lifting up of my hands as <f>ⓓ</f>the evening sacrifice! </t>
Psalm 141-3 <pb/><t><f>ⓔ</f> Set a guard, O LORD, over my mouth; </t><t><f>ⓕ</f>keep watch over the door of my lips!</t>
Psalm 141-4 <t><f>ⓖ</f> Do not let my heart incline to any evil, </t><t>to busy myself with wicked deeds </t><t>in company with men who <f>ⓗ</f>work iniquity, </t><t>and <f>ⓘ</f>let me not eat of their delicacies! </t>
Psalm 141-5 <pb/><t><f>ⓙ</f> Let a righteous man strike me — it is a kindness; </t><t>let him rebuke me — it is oil for my head; </t><t>let my head not refuse it. </t><t>Yet <f>ⓚ</f>my prayer is continually against their evil deeds.</t>
Psalm 141-6 <t>When their judges are <f>ⓛ</f>thrown over the cliff, <f>[1]</f> </t><t>then they shall hear my words, for they are pleasant.</t>
Psalm 141-7 <t>As when one plows and breaks up the earth, </t><t>so shall our bones <f>ⓜ</f>be scattered at the mouth of Sheol. <f>[2]</f> </t>
Psalm 141-8 <pb/><t>But <f>ⓝ</f>my eyes are toward you, O GOD, my Lord; </t><t><f>ⓞ</f>in you I seek refuge; leave me not defenseless! <f>[3]</f></t>
Psalm 141-9 <t>Keep me from <f>ⓟ</f>the trap that they have laid for me </t><t>and from the snares of evildoers!</t>
Psalm 141-10 <t>Let the wicked <f>ⓠ</f>fall into their own nets, </t><t>while I pass by safely. </t>